library_note: A leaf used as an ingredient for first-aid medicines. It can be easily found on any high ground.

library_note: The interior of the hard shell is filled with sweet juice, and it's enjoyed by adults and children alike as a beverage.
name: Palma Fruit

library_note: A fruit that tastes like fresh cream. The disadvantage is that it has a fluffy texture, so it goes bad easily.

library_note: A mushroom named because of its dark blue like the night sky and because the speckled pattern looked like a lady.

library_note: A super extreme mushroom with a reproductive power so high that it can fully cover a piece of land shortly after it starts to grow.

library_note: A mushroom whose cap is made of crystal. The cap is very hard and not edible, but it can be used for decoration.
name: Jewel Mushroom

library_note: A mushroom whose tip looks like a crown. Some people call it the 'king mushroom.'

library_note: A starfish with multiple thorns on its back. Because of its resemblance with Uni, it gained this name.

library_note: A subspecies of Uni. Because it's a type of sea creature, it can be caught in seawater.

library_note: A giant fish with wing-like fins. Despite its kind smile, it's rather ferocious.

library_note: A rare fish that inhabits waterfronts deep inside ruins. An endangered species that tastes very good if simmered.

library_note: A bee with a rose red part. Its carnivorous and has a poison strong enough to kill small animals.
name: Rose Bee

library_note: A giant insect with its entire body wrapped by a strong shell. It stays nonchalant if taunted by kids.

library_note: A dragon-looking insect. While its appearance may mislead many people, it's actually just an insect.

library_note: A mantis with feathers that look like a red cloak. Contrary to its appearance, it's surprisingly friendly.

library_note: A thread ball made by a spider by wrapping its arms around it. It's now stiff.

library_note: The staff Ryza used during her first adventure.  It looks the same, but it is incredible powerful.
name: Celestial Seeker

library_note: The staff Ryza used last summer. An improved version that looks the same but was enhanced with advanced technology.
name: Sparkling Reverie

library_note: The most powerful staff made with the cream of alchemy, designed to put an end to the war of the people of the Age of God.
name: Agnes Luce

library_note: Klaudia's favorite bow. An item without any special protrusion, but it is easy to use.
name: Ciel Shoot

library_note: A bow that has higher shooting speed and accuracy than her favorite bow.
name: Yale Soar

library_note: A bow that is transparent like crystal. It is rather heavy, which reduces recoil when shooting.
name: Croiselt

library_note: The bow used by Klaudia last summer.  It looks the same, but its power has been enhanced.
name: Astrumnox

library_note: A bow that is light like air and shoots powerful arrows.  No living creature can survive an arrow shot with this.
name: Astral Regalia

library_note: Lent's favorite long sword. It is quite heavy and will deliver an undefendable blow.
name: Smite Blade

library_note: A long sword that yields a special power. It releases an unusual aura.
name: Sword of Rupture

library_note: The sword Lent was using four years ago. It looks the same, but it is incomparably more powerful.
name: Lord Guardian

library_note: The sword Lent was using last summer. It has been finely adjusted to make it easier to use.
name: Demon Ender

library_note: A long sword used by Samuel in his mercenary days. A masterpiece made by a master swordsmith.
name: Liese Divider

library_note: Twin swords with the length of knives. Easy to carry and ideal for quick maneuvers.
name: Sharp Edge

library_note: After being reinforced, it gained considerable slashing and stabbing powers.
name: Paradiera

library_note: Twin swords made with the moon as a motif. Their blades are cold as moonlight.
name: Luna Solis

library_note: Twin swords used by Tao last summer. They've been improved to suit Tao's current strength.
name: Amphisbaena

library_note: It is a short sword and an axe, so they are not exactly twin swords, but they can be used as such without any problem.
name: Ifestio

library_note: A special sword with a hilt and blade of almost the same length.  It is hard to handle and not used by many people.
name: Aristoclite

library_note: A long-hilt-sword with improved sharpness. Its power is demonstrated when used by a master.
name: Herzog

library_note: A long-hilt-sword with a jagged blade. A terrifying sword that leaves horrible wounds.
name: Might of Heaven

library_note: A long-hilt-sword that Patty used to use. Its sharpness and strength remain the same, but it is now easier to handle.
name: Edel Schwert

library_note: Sword that lies between a long sword and a long-hilt-sword. With the use of centrifugal force, even short people can use it.
name: Efflorescence

library_note: A short staff with excellent maneuverability and sturdiness that is used for self-defense rather than as a weapon.
name: Wise Wand

library_note: A short staff that can be used both for self-defense and as a weapon. The thorn at the tip is unusually pointed.
name: Educator

library_note: An enhanced version of the short staff formerly used by Empel. It feels light like air when handling.
name: Occult Wisdom

library_note: A short staff that can be used for thrusting and slashing. It is powerful enough to crush enemy's ordinary swords and axes.
name: Nachfolger

library_note: The magic power of connected crystals is constantly flowing, enhancing the power of this short staff.
name: Genesis Staff

library_note: Lila's claws. A weapon made not for scratching but for ripping up.
name: Trisker

library_note: With simple improvement, its slicing power was successfully enhanced.
name: Aurora

library_note: Claws that Lila used to use.  An enhanced version made with a stronger material.
name: Oren Herald

library_note: Claws made after dragon scales and nails.  It can slice anything.
name: Ventiska

library_note: Claws with a porcelain texture. Valuable both as a weapon and a fine piece of art.
name: Nevernoche

library_note: A one-handed sword used by Bos. It is a mass-produced item, but is used by many due to its sturdiness.
name: Onyx Blade

library_note: A sword with a deep-red blade. Made with a metal that looks blood-stained.
name: Lysil Edge

library_note: A single-edged long sword. Because of its unusually hard blade, a blow with the back side of the blade has the same power.
name: Baron's Light

library_note: A double-blade long sword. Its sharp crystal-like blade can easily slice rocks.
name: Unfold

library_note: A legendary sword that is said to have sliced many enemies in the hands of a noble warrior in ancient past.
name: Lost Alucard

library_note: An iron folding-fan. A weapon that can be used as an iron pipe when folded and as a sharp blade when open.
name: Iron Fan

library_note: An iron folding-fan with a cherry-blossom-colored fabric attached. It can make enemies put off their guard with its looks.
name: Purple Orchid

library_note: A fine-looking iron folding-fan that could be owned by upper-class people. Sturdy, but very light.
name: Scarlet Heaven

library_note: A green iron folding-fan. Its structure allows it to be used not only to cut and hit but also be thrown.
name: Jing Qing Fan

library_note: An iron folding-fan with Lamberti Family's crest. Born from the combination of craftsmanship and alchemy.
name: Shrine Maiden's Dance

library_note: A large axe. Rather than slice enemies, it was designed to crush them with its power and weight.
name: Wild Axe

library_note: An axe that has the color of blood to begin with, but unlearned people often get the wrong idea.
name: Daybreak

library_note: It was made by enlarging the blade of an axe to make it much more powerful.
name: Estacado

library_note: A battle axe that is said to have been used by knights of a powerful kingdom. It can slice enemies with the blade on both sides or stab them.
name: Elde Divide

library_note: An axe mainly made with bones. This battle axe made with dragon bones can crush almost anything.
name: Diamantis

library_note: A war hammer with a heavy tip. Being struck with this must be horrific.
name: Moon Quake

library_note: A war hammer with the same hardness but slightly lighter for better handling.
name: Crepusclype

library_note: A thorny war hammer. I think this item requires no further explanation.
name: Gravimarius

library_note: A war hammer with an unusual shape. The opposite side of the flat part is just stylish.
name: Elder Lily

library_note: A war hammer made with rare materials. It does not look like a hammer because of it's unique shape.
name: Raventoad

library_note: A wand with enhanced parts that yield a special power. It must be useful in adventures.
name: Mistral Cane

library_note: A bow that yields a special power. The power inside it is mysterious.
name: Etoile Filant

library_note: A long sword with a red blade. It was made focused on being simply powerful.
name: Hashbringer

library_note: Twin swords that yield a special power. They can also be thrown as spinning swords.
name: Vita Reaper

library_note: A long-hilt-sword that yields a special power. The blade is covered, but...
name: Folklore

library_note: A short staff that yields a special power. It is decorated with birds.
name: Windword

library_note: Claws that yield a special power. They got bigger because of the armor.
name: Crimson Mist

library_note: A one-handed sword that yields a special power. Countless small swords are attached.
name: Void Punisher

library_note: An iron folding-fan that yields a special power. The edge is sharp as a blade.
name: Self-defense Fans

library_note: A battle axe that yields a special power. A new blade has been added.
name: Brute Veil

library_note: A war hammer that yields a special power. It looks like it is not useful for normal hitting attacks.
name: Solmarkt

library_note: Clothes worn by rich and noble people. Not commonly seen on Kurken Island.
name: Noble Tunic

library_note: Leather armor with exceptional versatility that's easy to move in. It's made to protect only the vital parts of the body.
name: Leather Protector

library_note: Armor made by combining the bones of beasts and monsters together. It's quite durable but not very pleasant to wear.
name: Bone Armor

library_note: A robe made for mages. It's made of a thick fabric that provides good protection but is still easy to move around in.
name: Mage's Robe

library_note: A cuirass that has been used for a long time. Still worn by low-ranked soldiers.
name: Soldier's Cuirass

library_note: Alloy-made bulky armor. So easy to make that even blacksmith apprentices can mass produce it.
name: Radiant Plate

library_note: An outfit made from materials obtained from pixies and spirits. It provides some amount of healing to the wearer.
name: Fairy Cloak

library_note: Double-layered light armor. Below the fabric made of strong thread material is a chain mail.
name: Chainmail Cloak

library_note: Armor said to be worn by foreign knights. Contrary to its appearance, it's easy to move in.
name: Foreign Armor

library_note: A vestment made for high-ranking priests. Not actually worn by elves.
name: Elven Robe

library_note: An outfit made for those who make long trips. It's specially made to assist the movements of the wearer.
name: Moonlight Cloak

library_note: Armor made with a large volume of precious dragon material. Because few units have been made, it stands out a lot when worn.
name: Dragoon Mail

library_note: An outfit that is worn as a symbol of the rank of the highest-ranking priests. It's made solely with materials containing large amounts of magical power.
name: Kruger Cloak

library_note: Light armor that is said to absorb sound and light, allowing its wearer to blend into the darkness of night.
name: Meuchelmolder

library_note: Extravagant armor that uses the hardest metal in existence. It's stronger than even dragon scales.
name: Armanoir

library_note: A charm that imitates an Uni. It uses a real Uni, and is a very popular gift.
name: Uni Charm

library_note: As an ornament, it's just a typical pendant. One feels less fatigue just by wearing it for some reason.
name: Energy Pendant

library_note: A ring that every adventurer knows very well. Its effect changes according to how it's made, and the higher the quality, the more expensive it gets.
name: Gnade Ring

library_note: A scarf that is said to make the whole body lighter when worn.
name: Phantom Scarf

library_note: A locket that is said to allow its wearer to shoulder the hardships of the person they want to protect if they put that person's picture in it.
name: Locket of Devotion

library_note: An amulet to wish for travelers' safety. It helps the feet feel less fatigued.
name: Migratory Charm

library_note: A necklace made with a lower volume of metal and designed to last a long time.
name: Quartz Necklace

library_note: A ring that enhances the magical powers of the wearer.
name: Warlock Ring

library_note: A bangle often worn by war-prone soldiers. It assists the movements of the muscles.
name: Warrior Bangle

library_note: A monocle that makes it possible to measure the distance to the enemy with accuracy and see their vulnerability.
name: Clairvoyance Monocle

library_note: A ring that is said to bring out the powers of items.
name: Harnal Ring

library_note: A choker formerly worn by a legendary strategist. Nowadays, it's a fashion item for women.
name: Warrior Choker

library_note: An amulet that provides the protection of the spirit of the four elements. It's extremely difficult to make.
name: Four Spirits Amulet

library_note: Cuffs that raise the morale of a group executing a task together, maximizing their efficiency.
name: Cluster Cuffs

library_note: A crown that makes the wearer look more dignified. It's surprisingly heavy, and wearing it for long periods makes the neck hurt.
name: Baron's Crown

library_note: An ornament that Kala, of the Oren, wanted. It's not rare in the human world.
name: Dragon Scale Necklace

library_note: A hoe that's snapped in half, or rather completely destroyed. How did it get used to get so badly damaged...?
name: Broken Hoe

library_note: A hoe fixed by Ryza. It's tougher than normal hoes and can be used to dig even boulders.
name: Light and Sturdy Hoe

library_note: A lamp that uses Fairystones. Federica's late father described it in a drawing.
name: Fairystone Light

library_note: A Fairystone Light improved by Ryza.
name: Fairystone Light EX

library_note: A pattern found on the Gate of Honor, drawn by Ryza. It's so poorly drawn that not even a polite compliment is suitable.
name: Scruffy Drawing

library_note: A hair clip with a Fairystone decoration of fire, the symbol of glasswork.
name: Flame Hair Clip

library_note: A brooch with a hammer adornment, the symbol of Fairystone decoration, made by glasswork.
name: Hammer Brooch

library_note: A highly concentrated solution that contains more magic than standard Duet Stock Solution.
name: Duet Stock Solution+

library_note: A solvent with higher concentration than that of Duet Solvent Solution. It allows for even more detailed processing.
name: Duet Solvent Solution EX

library_note: Material found in the ruins of Nemed. It's said to harbor immense powers.
name: Seeds of Light

library_note: An improved version of Seeds of Light with the capacity to suppress the explosive power they harbor.
name: Seeds of Light EX

library_note: A monitoring device installed by the Chief that stops the function of Clairvoyance.
name: Disturbing Bell

library_note: A pseudo-gate generator devised by Emil. It looks like it does not work the way its.
name: Emil's Tablet

library_note: A book left by Emil, detailing why Empel has an artificial arm. Its written in symbols.
name: Emil's Book

library_note: Metal used in the heart of Faurre's devices. It's a strong material with very good power transmission properties.
name: True Silver

library_note: A device that works as a guide to the Code of the Universe. It was dropped by a part of the Code of the Universe.
name: Chart of Another Sky

library_note: The necklace that Ryza gave to Fi last summer. It's worn out after just one year.
name: Fi's Necklace

library_note: Fi's Necklace repaired. A simple necklace, without any special effect.
name: Shiny Necklace

library_note: A pinwheel given by some people to our beloved children, along with a song, wishing for their happiness in the future.
name: Dancing Bird Pinwheel

library_note: The Fairystone Compass that has been processed with True Silver. It became more resistant to damage.
name: Silver Crystal

library_note: A tool that shows the location of the Code of the Universe gate, created by improving the Chart of Another Sky.
name: Celestial Globe of Another Sky

library_note: Very sturdy wood. Suitable for use as a building material.
name: High Quality Wood

library_note: Building materials for the construction of a new inn in the village of Rasenboden.
name: Sturdy Wood

library_note: A device used in the construction of Kurken Island. It's completely broken and beyond repair.
name: Broken Ancient Artifact

library_note: An improved purifier made by Ryza. An engineer, not necessarily an alchemist, can fix it.
name: New Purifier

library_note: An item found in the forest by the late husband of an old lady who lives in Sardonica.
name: Broken Light

library_note: A lamp made based on a recipe left by the alchemist who founded the city of Sardonica.
name: Lamp of the Beginning

library_note: Machine textbook of the people of the Age of God made for the Oren. For beginners, but making the machines is difficult.
name: Age of God Manual

library_note: Bones of an old dragon buried in a shrine of dragons in the Underworld. This dragon was unable to return to the world of humans and died.
name: Dragon Bone Fragment

library_note: A jewel made by processing bones of old dragons. It harbors the magical powers of powerful old dragons.
name: Ancient Dragon Gem

library_note: A box to store things inside. Neither the box or the objects stored ever deteriorate.
name: Indestructible Box

library_note: An auxiliary device for Empel. It smooths the movement of an artificial arm.
name: Auxiliary Prosthesis

library_note: A large and substantial lump of meat. It offers the original taste of meat.
name: Wild Meat on the Bone

library_note: An illustration book left by Federica's father. It was abandoned in the forest for a long time.
name: Father's Album

library_note: A purifier that is attached to desalination equipment. It takes the water quality back to the level when there was a fountain in Kurken Island.
name: Desalination Equipment EX

library_note: Federica's pendant. It bears a traditional Sardonican crest.
name: Federica's Pendant

library_note: A special coral found on a reef island. Has strong water purification powers.
name: High Quality Coral Stone

library_note: A high-purity solvent made from rainbow-colored liquid. Used to fuse Fairystones and glass.
name: "Agnes Luce" Recipe

library_note: A giant rice ball in the shape of a bomb. The filling is inside is a surprise.
name: Packed Rice

library_note: A skewer with grilled chicken and vegetables. Available with sauce or salt.
name: Roasted Chicken

library_note: A hamburger made with plenty of meat from wild animals. It has a smell unique to wild meat.
name: Gibier Burger

library_note: A sandwich with simple ingredients. It tastes almost the same, no matter who makes it.
name: Mixed Sandwich

library_note: Smoked meat with a satisfying taste. A precious food for adventurers because it can be stored for long periods.
name: Smoked Meat

library_note: A simple pizza with dried meat and cheese. The ones with extra cheese are popular, it seems.
name: Dried Meat Pizza

library_note: Carpaccio made of fresh fish. It's the perfect dish for the summer with its refreshing taste.
name: Fresh Fish Carpaccio

library_note: Pot-au-feu with summer vegetables. It's tasty, but you'll sweat a lot if you eat it on a warm day.
name: Summer Veggie Stew

library_note: Green pasta made with the image of a forest in mind. Vegetables were kneaded into the dough as well.
name: Forest Green Pasta

library_note: Paella with plenty of seafood. Very popular among seafood lovers.
name: Seafood Paella

library_note: The color makes it look super spicy, but it's actually mild, with a condensed umami flavor.
name: Red Chili Soup

library_note: Steak grilled on a hot crystal plate. It does not leave burn marks or cause oil splatter, but the oil makes it easy for the steak to slide off.
name: Steak on Crystal

library_note: A dish that is simply a huge whole roasted fish, but it's one of the most popular, perhaps because of how it looks.
name: Roasted Monster Fish

library_note: Omelette rice with demi-glace sauce. A standard menu item that is found in almost any store.
name: Beef Omelette Rice

library_note: Vegetables and meat simmered in white sauce. Stew fans will definitely like this one too.
name: White Sauce Ragu

library_note: A cute chick doll. It has the perfect size for a hug pillow.
name: Chick Doll

library_note: An ornament made by sculpting a crystal. When placed by a window, the shadow of the pattern is projected on the floor.
name: Crystal Object

library_note: Dolls of fairies. Because all are handmade, each face is slightly different.
name: Fairy Doll

library_note: It looks, feels, and smells like jelly. But it's purely for decoration and cannot be eaten.
name: Puni Jelly

library_note: A doll made to look exactly like a real Puni. It's said that not even the person who made it can distinguish it from the real thing.
name: Puni Doll

library_note: A stand designed to have an object be placed on it for the purpose of being seen and admired.
name: Exhibition Stand

library_note: Lighting equipment with the shape of a lantern. The fire that is the light source is also fake.
name: Hanging Lantern

library_note: A small round table for quick meals. It only has room for tea and snacks.
name: Round Table

library_note: A luxurious leather-covered sofa. It looks hard, but it's so soft that your body sinks into it.
name: Leather Sofa

library_note: The finest sofa designed to provide perfect comfort. If you sit once, you will not feel like standing up.
name: Chic Sofa

library_note: A low table with a design that is not too flashy or too simple and yet has presence.
name: Elegant Low Table

library_note: A large pendulum clock. Because it rings every hour, it's the perfect piece of furniture for those who care about time.
name: Pendulum Clock

library_note: A full 88-key piano. The keys are light so that children and beginners can play it.
name: Piano

library_note: A single bed with a simple design. After a few years, it starts to feel cramped.
name: Cute Bed

library_note: A luxurious bed made for aristocrats. It's superior sleeping comfort is unforgettable.
name: Extravagant Bed

library_note: A barrel, as you know! Whenever you touch or see it, you say 'barrel.'
name: Barrel

library_note: A fancy bench. It was designed to match lawns.
name: Fashionable Bench

library_note: A table made to be used in gardens. Apparently, it's often used indoors as well.
name: Garden Table

library_note: A pot with seasonal flowers. If not watered every day, they dry out very easily.
name: Potted Plant

library_note: A plush toy modelled after the Oren. It seems the person who it was modelled after also owns one.
name: Oren Doll

library_note: A small bell to notify when the food is ready. It's noisy if rung in excess.
name: Dinner Bell

library_note: A decorative object modelled after a legendary sword that only the brave can draw. The blade is not present.
name: Decorative Sword

library_note: A bed used in high-end inns in the land of everlasting summer. It provides good sleep even on sweltering nights.
name: Resort Bed

library_note: A sofa used in high-end inns. It's meant for people to sit and relax for long periods.
name: Resort Sofa

library_note: A cheap table with a slightly high-end table cloth.
name: Table with Tablecloth

library_note: A pot with a small palm tree. Because it does not grow large, it does not produce nuts.
name: Potted Palm

library_note: A music stand used by maestros and flutists. Just place a music score, and it becomes a piece of interior decoration.
name: Music Stand

library_note: It appears to be the manuscript of an ancient book, but the letters on it no longer exist, so it requires translation.
name: Giant Manuscript

library_note: A pot with a tree that bears a small fruit. It's said that fairies come to eat those fruits.
name: Pixie Pot

library_note: A chair designed after the chairs on which the great elementals sit. Because it's design-focused, it's not comfortable.
name: Great Elemental's Chair

library_note: A decorative object in the shape of moving stars. It's said that all astronomers have one.
name: Celestial Body Model

library_note: A picture of a rural scenery. Because it's a simple rural landscape, it's not among the most popular.
name: Farm Photo

library_note: A picture of scenes of a rural town. Its a famous landscape, but nobody knows where the picture was taken.
name: Countryside Photo

library_note: A rocking chair made with lightweight material. It can be easily moved anywhere.
name: Rocking Chair

library_note: A very common sofa. It has a wide seat that is long enough to accommodate three people comfortably.
name: Cute Sofa

library_note: A very common blackboard. It can be used not only for classes but also personal study and work.
name: Blackboard

library_note: Everybody has seen this, but nobody has ever met the weapon craftsman who it was modeled after.
name: Blacksmith Statue

library_note: Since it's alive, it naturally needs to be looked after. Should be raised as an important family member, not a piece of furniture.
name: Goat

library_note: A fully baked bread. It's soft inside, and even the lightly roasted crust is tasty.
name: Crisp Bun

library_note: A stuffed animal in the shape of a pumpkin-headed fairy. A doll modelled after a mischievous fairy.
name: Pumpkin Doll

library_note: A sphere with the map of the entire world. Kurken Island is so small that it appears as a dot.
name: Globe

library_note: A piece of furniture in the shape of a cannon. It's said that it does not shoot, but it actually shoots.
name: Transport Cannon

library_note: An intensely sweet specialty doughnut made in the capital. Empel's favorite.
name: Ashra Donut

library_note: Large Kurken Fruits that were grown through proper nutrition and cultivation environment over a long period.
name: Giant Luceaux Seed

library_note: Sweets that were put together with an exquisite balance. If touched carelessly, the pile will easily crumble.
name: Mountain of Sweets

library_note: A horn that is said to have been made of a dragon horn. In reality, it's made of animal antlers.
name: Exotic Horn

library_note: A basket full of apple-scented potpourri. Naturally, it's not edible.
name: Apple Basket

library_note: Actual armor worn by knights. It can be worn for self-defense, in case of emergency.
name: Knight's Armor

library_note: A big teddy bear. Because of its high price, many girls long for it.
name: Teddy Bear

library_note: Please look at the picture rather than the frame. It's a nostalgic photo of an important memory.
name: Beautiful Picture Frame

library_note: A convenient broom that moves and cleans any dirt by itself, when it finds it.
name: Mysterious Broom

library_note: A gramophone with a special focus on the acoustics. It's a popular piece of furniture, even among those who do not own records.
name: Phonograph

library_note: A weasel doll. It appears to be quite popular among people who cannot have pets.
name: Weasel Doll

library_note: It's dazzling, and the model looks uncomfortably hot. It surely attracts unnecessary attention.
name: Shiny Bust

library_note: Nobody knows who the model was for this glittering bust.
name: Sparkling Bust

library_note: A picture of the capital. It seems to have been taken in the morning, when there were few people around.
name: Photo of the Capital

library_note: A stuffed toy made with the same weight, texture, and softness as Fi's.
name: Fi Doll

library_note: A small house made from various sweets. If overeaten, it can no longer hold the shape of a house.
name: Candy House

library_note: A normal cork board that can be found anywhere.
name: Mini Cork Board

library_note: An accessory to organize books upright. A slightly convenient piece of furniture.
name: Books And Bookends

library_note: A fancy tea set. Because the appearance was prioritized, it's hard to wash the pot.
name: Tea Set

library_note: A device that can be useful in synthesis. Not normally used in synthesis involving alchemy.
name: Synthesis Eqp Set

library_note: A pile of Uni. They work as preserved food and for self-defense.
name: Basket of Uni

library_note: A mushroom-shaped lamp. The cap part issues a soft glow.
name: Mushroom Shaped Lamp

library_note: A distorted devil doll. It's warm when hugged.
name: Small Devil Doll

library_note: Boomerang with bird feathers. Aerodynamic and easily strikes its targets.
name: Downwind

library_note: A crystal ball that can be imbued with magic. It changes color and attribute depending on the magic put into it.
name: Rainbow Lapis

library_note: A flask that contains the soul of a three-headed monster. Said to take the soul of an enemy once it has been defeated.
name: Cerberus Spirit

library_note: An arrow made of dragon materials. Powerful enough to fly while gouging the ground, but may break the bow.
name: Draconic Arrow

library_note: Throwing machete. Is it the machete's weight that tires its wielder, or does it drain their strength?
name: Maleficus

library_note: A parchment containing a powerful incantation that can be activated by reading it aloud. Make any mistakes and the spell will not activate.
name: Calamity Code

library_note: Cocoa sweet enough to wake you from a deep sleep. There are even some who prefer such sweetness normally.
name: Sugar Drip

library_note: Portable fountain overflowing with a medicinal solution. Hard to drink from, but very effective!
name: Eternal Spring

library_note: An instrument that emits soothing tones. It is quite heavy and drains the player's strength.
name: Suonare

library_note: A cracker that makes a loud bang!
name: Voltage Liberator

library_note: A huge weathervane. It is clearly very heavy, and it is said that the wind blows in whatever direction it points.
name: Windsong Fowl

library_note: A bell that normally does not ring when shaken, but in an emergency, it emits a calming chime.
name: Bell of Tranquility

library_note: A pretty flower that, when planted, sucks up so many nutrients from the soil that it kills the others around it.
name: Lovely Blossom

library_note: Is it an object, or some kind of energy mass? It seems rather unstable, and it emits powerful pulses.
name: Neutronenstern

library_note: A jar that is extremely lightweight for its size. They say looking at what's inside will make you feel sick.
name: Violet Cauldron

library_note: A tree branch that is said to suppress magic. However, there isn't much point in using it by itself.
name: Seal Branch

library_note: An old dragon's claw. It looks ancient, but its sharpness has been honed over many years.
name: Old Dragon's Claw

library_note: A mysterious stone clothed in the power of water. Since it is the same temperature as the water it always feels cool and soothing.
name: Water Stone

library_note: A unique metal that absorbs sound. It is a valuable building material.
name: Silence Steel

library_note: A white flower that gleams beautifully in the moonlight. Creatures fascinated by its beauty inhabit the surroundings.
name: Verdant Moonflower

library_note: Water in a gourd. The water is said to have special effects.
name: Heavenly Seawater

library_note: A fish that appears transparent in water. For this reason, is extremely difficult to catch.
name: Clearfish

library_note: A type of fruit shaped like a bird flapping its wings. Popular as a lucky charm.
name: Pine Fruit

library_note: A rock that contains a large amount of salt. The purer the rock is, the more intense its pink coloring.
name: Melocotone

library_note: A brightly colored clam shaped like a star. Popular not only as a decorative material, but also as food.
name: Star Clam

library_note: An insect that feeds on gemstones. They increase the purity of the gemstones they eat, storing them within their bodies.
name: Gemeater

library_note: A mushroom with a blade-like cap. In fact, their caps are so sharp that they can be used as knives.
name: Tsurugi Mushroom

library_note: A stone so light that it floats on water. Shaped like a flower petal, it is almost indistinguishable from a real petal.
name: Floating Petal Stone

library_note: A metal that is said to never rust. Characterized by its bright green hue.
name: Verdeum Metal

library_note: A flower with seeds that look like cotton wool. Widely distributed since its seeds are carried by the wind.
name: Wool Flower

library_note: A plant whose thick leaves contain a bactericidal solution.
name: Cleaner Plant

library_note: Very bitter, but effective for both wounds and colds. It is so bitter that few can consume it in its natural state.
name: Medicinal Sap

library_note: Has a hard, scaly bark. Its toughness makes it difficult to harvest.
name: Immortal Sapling

library_note: Small rain clouds drifting above the ground. They produce quite heavy rainfall for their size.
name: Blessed Clouds

library_note: Wooden ornament. Its use other than as an ornament is unknown, but perhaps it could be a wood substitute?
name: Carved Relic

library_note: A plant that resembles a giant sickle. Extremely toxic, so approach with caution.
name: Reaper's Scythe

library_note: Threads found after rain and in areas of high humidity. Thin but strong enough to withstand strong winds.
name: Heavenly Rain Thread

library_note: An object that has the power to distort the space around it. Contains a powerful energy and quite unstable.
name: Unstable Lump

library_note: Nut that can be used as a fire-starter or fuel. Valued by adventurers.
name: Ignis Nut

library_note: An old scroll. Nothing is written on it, but the paper itself contains powerful magic.
name: Ancient Scroll

library_note: A stone material with molten metal poured into fine crevices. Harder and more ductile than ordinary stone.
name: Edelhard

library_note: A versatile base for liquid medicine. Can be combined with other drugs to produce medicines with excellent healing properties.
name: Medica Solution

library_note: A poison so deadly that a single drop can kill even the most ferocious of beasts. It vaporizes into an odorless gas when left at room temperature.
name: Toxited

library_note: A mysterious sand that turns into jelly when soaked in liquid. Easy to store in dry sand form.
name: Jelly Sand

library_note: A bright crimson liquid at room temperature. When heated it becomes volatile, type of an explosive.
name: Crimson Birth

library_note: Coal that contains more oil than usual. Once ignited, it burns hotter and for a longer amount of time.
name: Riot Coal

library_note: A sort of yarn made with extremely hard mineral components. Its high durability compensates for its relative inflexibility.
name: Vajra Wire

library_note: Potpourri made from plants that are considered sacred. It is said to have a calming and relaxing effect.
name: Lumiere Potpourri

library_note: A device that allows the flow of gases of various compositions in and out. Each type can be stored separately.
name: Ideal Unit

library_note: Secret dragon extract that can serve as either poison or medicine depending on how it is used.
name: Dragon's Tears

library_note: At first glance, it looks like trendy formal wear, but various weapons are hidden inside it.
name: Antique Style

library_note: Hunter's equipment that allows the user to move lightly even in poor environments. Dustproof, waterproof, and heat-resistant.
name: Hunter's Wear

library_note: This is a unique improvement upon the royal court's luxurious equipment. Flaunt your power with colorful jewels!
name: Luminous Gold Armor

library_note: Used by aristocrats for the glove-throwing tradition when challenging someone to a duel.
name: Immortal Gloves

library_note: A special flower that does not wither naturally and is often used as a good luck charm.
name: Fleur Corsage

library_note: A metal lamp that contains great magical power. After a long enough period of time, it may even become a home to a spirit.
name: Lamp of Force

library_note: Rare jewelry found mainly in the kingdom's western region. Some see the illusion of a shimmering border between the purple and yellow.
name: Aurora Jewel

library_note: Extremely powerful painkiller, but even the slightest error in its composition can cause it to become toxic to humans.
name: GlÃ¼ck Potion

library_note: A mysterious candelabra that continues to burn without extinguishing and is not hot to the touch.
name: Torch of the Ages

library_note: High-grade thread used by royals. Light as a cloud, yet highly durable.
name: Royal Spun Thread

library_note: The white sand that blankets Rosca Island. It feels more like ash than regular sand.
name: White Sand of Eternity

library_note: A ball of dry grass blown by the wind. It grows by assimilating other plants in its path.
name: Traveling Grass

library_note: Metal mined only on Rosca Island. It is thought to be specially formed by its unique environment, but details are unknown.
name: White Sand Metal

library_note: An ore with a purple part that contains a lot of magic power and a glassy yellow part.
name: Ametrite

library_note: Ore that was left behind by the people who used to live here. It is not in its original form, but it is of great cultural value.
name: Forgotten Pottery

library_note: Each of the three tails contains a venom with different properties, any of which will work on any creature.
name: Desert Cleaner

library_note: It grows by storing a small amount of water in its body, which is red inside. Valuable as precious moisture in arid regions.
name: Trifruit

library_note: The brighter its red flower blooms, the more nutritious it is considered. Sold as a vegetable.
name: Cactus Blossom

library_note: It is said to be the souls of the dead. When released into the sky, they always fly in one direction.
name: Mortal Anima

library_note: Lower jawbone strengthened by crushing rocks. Countless scars are evidence of its violent history.
name: Shark Bone

library_note: Meat of monsters from Rosca Island. A favorite of Dian's.
name: Exotic Meat

library_note: A copy of translated literature obtained from travels around Rosca Island.
name: Kala's Translated Texts (Copy)

library_note: A rare material obtained from the golden puni on the capital outskirts. Enthusiasts everywhere jump with joy when they manage to get their hands on it.
name: Golden Puniball

library_note: Neutralizer dyed crimson that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
name: Crimson Neutralizer

library_note: Neutralizer as clear as the azure sky that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
name: Azure Neutralizer

library_note: Neutralizer that is bright green and has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
name: Emerald Neutralizer

library_note: Neutralizer imbued with a thunderous strength that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron.
name: Thunder Neutralizer

library_note: An ingot that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, making it even stronger than before.
name: Hard Ingot

library_note: Cloth that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, giving it unprecedented flexibility.
name: Soft Cloth

library_note: Fiber that has acquired additional power from an ancient cauldron, making it strong enough to withstand any weight.
name: Strong Alchemy Fibers

library_note: Mixed oil that burns longer than ever before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
name: Flame Mixing Oil

library_note: Medica Powder with higher potency than before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
name: Superior Medica Powder

library_note: Poisonous Liquid with higher potency than before, thanks to a formula brewed in an ancient cauldron.
name: Strong Poisonous Liquid

library_note: A crystal that can only be found within a sandstorm.^00It seems to contain a strange sort of power...
name: Sandstorm Crystal

library_note: A new key created by Ryza in the land of swirling white sand. It works even upon withered ground.
name: White Tower Key

library_note: A key with a reddish-black ore that appears to be the color of blood.
name: Bloodstone Key

library_note: A key with white and black feathers on either side.
name: Fallen Angel Key

library_note: A key with a charm that seems to pull the beholder into a dream world.
name: Dream Key

library_note: A key that is said to be based on the image of the sun being eclipsed by the moon.
name: Eclipse Key

library_note: A key with an abundance of achromatic gemstones.
name: Colorless Crystal Key

library_note: A key created in the image of an angel, a legendary being.
name: Divine Wing Ruler Key

library_note: A key created envisioning the skies of another world.
name: Master of the Void Key

library_note: A key that contains the breath of life of the nature itself.
name: Cradle of Life Key

library_note: A cloudy white crystal with a power similar to that of the white moon that gives eternal life.
name: White Moon's Soul

library_note: An orb that contains the terrifying ability to pull things in and transport them to some other location.
name: Universe Sphere

library_note: A wood that is extremely lightweight but very durable. It doesn't even hurt if you drop it on your foot!
name: Fairywood

library_note: A heat-resistant container filled with magma. Not hot to the touch, but dangerous when opened.
name: Mini Volcano

library_note: A rare flower with seven-colored petals. Rumor has it that if you find one, your wish will come true.
name: Seven-Color Pansy

library_note: A tree with flowers that look like little fairies. Said to grow only in certain areas.
name: Fairy Sapling

library_note: A stone that combusts above a certain temperature. It must be kept in water so it won't ignite at room temperature.
name: Lava Rock

library_note: A mysterious stone that emits a bluish-white light. It is said to fall from the sky when the moon wanes.
name: Moon Fragment
